IBADAN  – Chief Adegboyega Adegoke, the Ajia Balogun of Ibadanland, on Tuesday, expressed commitment towards jobs creation for artisans in Oyo State as well as contribute his quota to the development of the traditional institution in Ibadanland. He stated this as he donated N5million worth of concrete blocks at the foundation stone laying ceremony for the construction of modern Traditional Council Building, tagged ‘Mini Mapo’ in Ibadan South West initiated by the former governor of Oyo State, High Chief Rashidi Ladoja. High Chief Ladoja, who is the Osi Olubadan of Ibadanland and Governor Seyi Makinde performed the foundation stone laying held at the Ibadan Southwest Local government Secretariat, Alesinloye, while the Olubadan of Ibadanland, Oba Saliu Adetunji Aje Ogungunniso 1 was the Chief Host and Chairman of the ceremony. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network